The paper discusses the feasibility, deployment, and operation of energy harvesting small cell networks, which are wireless networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses optimization and design methodologies, which are related to information theory, leading to the possibility of cs.IT (Information Theory) as the second likely category. The paper also discusses the challenges of deploying and operating small cell networks, which can be related to game theory, leading to the possibility of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as the third likely category. The paper also discusses the potential solutions and effective design methodologies, which can be related to control systems, leading to the possibility of cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the fourth likely category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of energy harvesting small cell networks in mobile applications, which can be related to multimedia, leading to the possibility of cs.MM (Multimedia) as the fifth likely category.
